Program: Omnibus
Title: The Assegai and the Redcoats
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376lvv
Last Broadcast Date: 01 April 1999
A look at the legacy of the 1879 Battle of Isandlwana between British Red Coats and Zulu warriors when the colonial power's advance across Southern African was temporarily halted by a part-time force of peasant farmers armed only with assegai (spears).